  "doc_id": "4656",
  "text": "The primary efficacy endpoint for the extension was the number and proportion of patients reaching LIC <5 mg Fe/g dw by the end of the extension. Additional analyses included assessment of the number and proportion of patients with LIC <3 mg Fe/g dw and the change in serum ferritin. LIC was measured at baseline then every 6 months using a validated R2 MRI technique (FerriScan®; Resonance Health, Perth, Australia) [CITATION_1] . Secondary endpoints included correlation of serum ferritin with LIC and change in LIC and serum ferritin in patients who interrupted therapy as a result of LIC <3 mg Fe/g dw or serum ferritin <100 ng/mL.",
